class Solution {
public:
    bool detectCapitalUse(string word) {
        int count = 0;
        for (char c : word) {
            if (isupper(c)) count++;
        }
        return count == 0 || count == word.size() || (count == 1 && isupper(word[0]));
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates through the string once, counting the number of uppercase letters. It then checks if the count is 0 (all lowercase), equal to the length of the string (all uppercase), or 1 and the first letter is uppercase (only first letter capitalized).

